source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SEQ_00<tab>Kohagi would like you to whack slow, then fast.
target: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SEQ_00<tab>ナマイ村のコハギは、冒険者に頼みたいことがあるようだ。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_TODO_00<tab>Obtain water serpent livers from the water serpents.
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_TODO_01<tab>Deliver the water serpent livers to Sentei.
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_000<tab>Could I ask you to help with a problem of mine? It concerns some water serpents that have recently infested the One River.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_000<tab>よろしければ、頼まれごとを引き受けてくれませんか？
実は「無二江」に、<var 28 ((BNpcName)) F2168201 /var>が棲みついてしまったようなのです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_001<tab>They used to only be found further to the west, but, for one reason or another, some have found their way closer to Namai.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_001<tab>以前は、もっと西の方が棲息地だったんですけれど、
天敵が出たのか、逃げてきたようでして……。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_002<tab>If prepared properly, they are quite delectable. However, there are far more in the river than one could ever hope to cook. No, their numbers must be controlled by other means.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_002<tab>食べると美味しいので、うれしくもあるのですが、
あまり増えてしまっても、それはそれで困るもの……。
そこで、3匹ほど「<var 28 ((BNpcName)) F2168201 /var>」を倒していただきたいのです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_003<tab>Please slay a few of them for me. Enough to stop them from taking the whole river for their own. Oh, and should you happen to get your hands on a few of their livers, please deliver them to my husband, Sentei.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_003<tab>もし、倒した際に「<var 28 ((EventItem)) F61E8D3F01 /var>」を手に入れたら、
私の旦那の「センテイ」に届けていただけないでしょうか？
あの人の大好物なんです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_004<tab>You will find him in the Drunken Toad to the east.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_004<tab>この村の東にある、酔いどれ蛙の船小屋にいるはずですから。
手間をかけさせてしまいますが、よろしくお願いいたします。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_005<tab>Should you happen to get your hands on a few of their livers, please deliver them to my husband, Sentei, in the Drunken Toad.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_KOHAGI_000_005<tab>無二江にいる「<var 28 ((BNpcName)) F2168201 /var>」を3匹倒していただけますか？
また、その際に「<var 28 ((EventItem)) F61E8D3F01 /var>」が手に入ったら、
村の東の小屋にいる「センテイ」に届けてあげてください。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_010<tab>Do you have business with me, traveler?
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_010<tab>なんだい？
俺に何か用でも？

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_011<tab>Water serpent livers! But why did you think to bring these to me?
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_011<tab>おっ、こいつは<var 28 ((EventItem)) F61E8D3F01 /var>じゃねえか！
どうしてこれを俺にくれるんだい？

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_012<tab>Ah, my wife put you up to it, did she? My sincerest thanks. I shall boil these and eat them shortly.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_012<tab>なるほど、コハギがあんたに頼んでたってわけか。
そいつはありがたい。
鍋で煮て食うのが大好きなんだよ。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_013<tab>Back in the days when I made my living transporting rice up and down the river, I used to slay any water serpents I saw and take them home to cook. Of course, that all stopped once the Empire blocked off the One River.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_013<tab>昔は、川船で米を運んで生計を立てながら、
たまに<var 28 ((BNpcName)) F2168201 /var>を見つけたら、斧で仕留めて土産にしてたもんだ。
……帝国軍がやってきて、無二江を封鎖しちまう前の話だがね。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_014<tab>It is thanks to nature and kind strangers like you that I am able to put food on my table these days. Thank you so much.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ407_02730_SENTEI_000_014<tab>とはいえ、豊かな自然と、あんたみたいな、
親切な人のおかげで、どうにか食っていけている……。
ありがたい話だよ、まったくな……。
